Class Individual

java.lang.Object
  com.mattharrah.gedcom4j.Individual

public class Individual
extends java.lang.Object

An individual person. Corresponds to the INDIVIDUAL_RECORD structure in the GEDCOM specification.

public Individual()
Method Detail

formattedName

public java.lang.String formattedName()
Get all the individual's names formatted as a single string. Names after the first one found are shown with "aka" in between each.

Returns:
a string with all the various names for the current individual

getAncestors

public java.util.Set<Individual> getAncestors()
Get a set of ALL the direct ancestors of the current individual, in all generations. Includes parents, and all their parents, and all their parents, and so on. Siblings, cousins, aunts/uncles, etc. are not included in the results.

Returns:
a set of ancestors for the current individual.

getDescendants

public java.util.Set<Individual> getDescendants()
Get all the direct blood-line descendants of the current individual, in all generations. Includes children, their children, their children, and so on. Spouses of descendants are not included in the results.

Returns:
a set of descendants for the current individual

getEventsOfType

public java.util.List<IndividualEvent> getEventsOfType(IndividualEventType type)
Get a list of events of the supplied type for this individual

Parameters:
type - the type of event to get
Returns:
a list of events of the specified type

getSpouses

public java.util.Set<Individual> getSpouses()
Get a set of spouses for the current individual. Always returns a set, although it may be empty. The returned set is in no particular order.

Returns:
a set of spouses for the current individual.
